tton%20mushrooms%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F285468%2Fgrow-organic-oyster-mushrooms-at-home-diy-earthen-pots-how-to%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoyster%20mushrooms%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20milky%20mushrooms.%20Button%20mushrooms%20thrive%20in%20cooler%20climates%2C%20while%20oyster%20and%20milky%20mushrooms%20flourish%20in%20warmer%20conditions%2C%20making%20it%20easy%20to%20choose%20the%20variety%20best%20suited%20to%20your%20local%20weather.%20People%20have%20given%20cultivating%20shiitake%20mushrooms%20a%20try%20as%20well!%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESetting%20up%20a%20small-scale%20mushroom%20farm%20is%20surprisingly%20simple%20and%20involves%20just%20six%20key%20steps%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E1.%20Choosing%20your%20mushroom%20variety%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBegin%20by%20selecting%20a%20mushroom%20type%20that%20aligns%20with%20your%20regional%20climate%20and%20personal%20preferences.%20Button%20mushrooms%20are%20ideal%20for%20cooler%20areas%2C%20while%20oyster%20mushrooms%20are%20more%20resilient%20and%20beginner-friendly.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E2.%20Composting%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComposting%20is%20the%20foundation%20of%20successful%20mushroom%20farming%20and%20must%20be%20done%20meticulously.%20This%20process%20is%20carried%20out%20in%20the%20open%20on%20flat%20trays%20with%20proper%20drainage%20to%20prevent%20liquid%20accumulation.%20To%20protect%20the%20compost%20from%20rain%2C%20ensure%20a%20covered%20or%20sheltered%20area.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompost%20can%20be%20either%20natural%20or%20synthetic.%20Synthetic%20compost%20involves%20a%20mix%20of%20wheat%20straw%2C%20bran%2C%20urea%2C%20gypsum%2C%20and%20calcium%20ammonium%20nitrate%20or%20ammonium%20sulphate.%20These%20materials%20are%20blended%20well%2C%20soaked%20using%20a%20sprinkling%20method%2C%20and%20piled%20up.%C2%